GIT
 is a Version Control System (VCS) for tracking changes in computer files
 can have multiple developers in a different network
 can determine who made and who changes
 can revert back anytime
 local & remote repository

Git bash is a command tool

Basic Commands on Local repository
$ git init // Initialize Local Git Repository and to use git commands
$ git add <file> // Add File(s) To Index or Staging area
$ git rm --cached <file> // Remove File(s) to the Index or Staging Area
$ git rm -r --cached . // Fixing .gitignore files
$ git status // Check Status Of Working Tree
$ git commit // Commit Changes In Index
& git --version // Gets the version
& git config --global user.name 'Gabriel Zeus Reyes'
& git config --global user.email 'gabrielzeusreyes@gmail.com'
& touch index.html // creates a file named 'index.html'

Remote repository Commands
$ git push //Push To Remote Repository such as Github
$ git pull //Pull Latest From Remote Repository
$ git clone //Clone Repository Into A New Directory

** To open the gitbash on the folder, right click the folder, thenn click Git Bash here

Adding files to the Staging:
$ git add <file> // Add File(s) To Index or Staging area
   ex. git add *.html
   	   git add . // Add all the files in the folder

Commiting files 
$ git commit // Commit Changes In Index
	** it will go to the VIM editor, then press I to insert something
	** remove the # infront of the text 'Initial commit'
	** press escape
	** then type :wq

$ git commit -m 'Your comment here'

Ignoring file for Git
create first a .gitignore file using touch .gitignore
then type the filename

Ignoreing a folder for Git
type /<folder name>

